{"title":"Orange Alpine EVO 155m travel single-pivot is their “most progressive Alpine to date”","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/30/orange-alpine-evo-155m-travel-single-pivot-is-their-most-progressive-alpine-to-date/","date":1627639218000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Orange Bikes are staying away from referring to the all-new Alpine EVO as an enduro bike. Preferring to remain on the fence, they say “it’s more versatile than that, but given a chance it will dominate any trail bike in challenging and aggressive terrain”. The 160mm fork is paired with a 155mm travel rear end delivered, as ever, by the classic Orange single-pivot. Before we get into the tech, here’s Joe Barnes giving the new Orange Alpine EVO a right seeing to…</p><p><span><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/T3HBLzOAyeo?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" ezoid=\"0.20324206056367533\"></iframe></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_266871\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266871\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange alpine evo joe barnes bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-629x420.jpg 629w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121109/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_007-Edit-629x420.jpg 629w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266871\">Joe Barnes’ Orange Alpine EVO 155mm travel single-pivot 27.5″ trail bike</figcaption></figure><p>Orange say the Alpine EVO has the most progressive suspension of any Alpine to date. That statement refers to the custom shock tune of course, as, like all Orange full suspension bikes, the single-pivot suspension platform on the Alpine EVO is linear. The Alpine EVO still runs 27.5″ wheels like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/27/dudes-of-hazzard-orange-alpine-6-and-switch-6-limited-ed-bikes-drop-with-mystery-shock/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Alpine 6</a>, but in a slightly shorter travel package with 160mm up front and 155mm out back.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018.jpg\" alt=\"orange alpine evo geometry long slack 155mm travel trail mtb single-pivot\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt