Joe-Barnes_018-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121115/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_018-629x420.jpg 629w\"></a></p><p>Those smaller suspension numbers are coupled with a slacker head tube angle, longer reach, longer chainstays and steeper seat tube angle to deliver a bike likely to be quite different in its ride character.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orange alpine evo 445mm chainstays 275 wheels\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-629x420.jpg 629w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-768x513.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-696x465.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-1068x713.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121122/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_021-629x420.jpg 629w\"></a></p><p>Across the S to XL frame size range, the head tube is a slack 63° while the seat tube angle sits upright at an effective 76°. On a size large, reach comes in at a very generous 495mm, with chainstays at 445mm (consistent across the range). Spec’d with a 37mm offset fork, wheelbase numbers come in significantly longer than those seen on the Alpine 6, at 1280mm in large. The BB drop is -17mm.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"orange alpine evo geometry chart\" width=\"1200\" height=\"857\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-297x212.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-800x571.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-120x86.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-768x548.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-696x497.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-1068x763.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-588x420.jpg 588w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-100x70.jpg 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-297x212.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-800x571.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-120x86.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-768x548.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-696x497.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-1068x763.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-588x420.jpg 588w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29120348/orange-alpine-evo-geometry-chart-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a></p><p>For the Alpine EVO, Orange have taken a new approach to the design of the swingarm. It still looks very much like an Orange swingarm of course, and it is still made from custom formed monocoque 6061-T6 aluminium. It is now asymmetric, however, with a lowered non-driveside chainstay, designed to better resist twisting under pedaling loads. Orange say it does this whilst maintaining the lateral flex that gives grip when the bike is leant over.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm.jpg\" alt=\"finite element analysis of new orangle alpine evo 155mm travel trail bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"761\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-297x188.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-800x507.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-120x76.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-768x487.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-696x441.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-1068x677.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-662x420.jpg 662w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-297x188.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-800x507.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-120x76.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-768x487.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-696x441.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-1068x677.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121931/fea-orange-alpine-evo-swingarm-662x420.jpg 662w\"></a></p><p>Orange relied heavily on finite element analysis during the frame’s development to fine-tune the lateral and longitudinal stiffness beyond the levels that they have achieved before. In addition to lowering the non-drive-side chainstay, Orange have further integrated the bearing housings and revised tube thicknesses, resulting in a 20% increase in longitudinal stiffness and a 15% increase in overall strength compared their previous construction methods. This improved stiffness ratio is said to aid pedal efficiency through a reduction in twisting and enhance shock performance, all without a weight penalty.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062.jpg\" alt=\"orangle alpine evo non drive side lowered chainstay asymmetric swingarm stiffer stronger\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1798\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-200x300.jpg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-800x1200.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-80x120.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-768x1151.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-1025x1536.jpg 1025w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-696x1043.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-1068x1600.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-280x420.jpg 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-200x300.jpg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-800x1200.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-80x120.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-768x1151.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-1025x1536.jpg 1025w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-696x1043.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-1068x1600.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29121135/Orange-Bikes-2022-Alpine-Evo-Joe-Barnes_062-280x420.jpg 280w\"></a></p><p>Orange also tell us that the frame’s asymmetric bearing housing means they can use a neutral pivot location with less drivetrain/suspension interaction, allowing the bike to pedal smoothly through the choppiest of terrain.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green.jpg\" alt=\"orange alpine evo le edition\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/29123218/orange-alpine-evo-le-launch-edition-model-pearlescent-green-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The Orange Alpine EVO is now available in the LE (Launch Edition) only, retailing at £5,900. It comes in with a pearlescent Stealth Green paint finish with a performance component package including:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>RockShox Lyrik Ultimate 160mm Fork</li><li>RockShox Super Deluxe Ultimate Shock</li><li>Shimano XT 1x12spd&nbsp; drivetrain with Hope Crankset</li><li>Shimano XT 4-Piston Brakes with 203mm/180mm rotors</li><li>SDG 150mm dropper post</li><li>Renthal/Hope/SDG finishing kit</li><li>New&nbsp;Strange Grappler Grips</li><li>Maxxis Minion EXO tyres</li><li>E13 rims on Hope Pro 4 hubs</li></ul><p>The Alpine EVO LE is available now from Orange dealers. We are waiting to hear more from Orange as to whether or not other, more affordable, models of the Alpine EVO will be made available in due course.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.orangebikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>OrangeBikes.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"56c10b51fa3750dfbbdd3b02a2b3f778ab87669860bee6807f87cc330cc24be8","category":"Cycling"}